Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["\<\
Analyzing LLM extraction (distillation) attacks: latent clustering & \
latency-based anomaly detection\
\>", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9820025470562134`*^9, 
  3.982002578238558*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fa74af95-f003-5c48-9784-\
72de9351ad14"],

Cell["by Ahmed Elbanna", "Author",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9820025865861206`*^9, 
  3.982002590021591*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"16a329cb-ce34-df46-814c-\
3fbd290a544a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Inspired by ",
 ButtonBox["OpenAI accusing DeepSeek of distilling its models",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.reuters.com/world/china/openai-accuses-deepseek-\
distilling-us-models-gain-advantage-bloomberg-news-2026-02-12/"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://www.reuters.com/world/china/openai-accuses-deepseek-distilling-us-\
models-gain-advantage-bloomberg-news-2026-02-12/"],
 ", this work investigates the mechanics of Large Language Model (LLM) \
distillation attacks by analyzing how attackers systematically extract \
underlying reasoning capabilities from frontier models. By systematically \
analyzing API responses this notebook exposes extraction footprints such as \
predictable inter-query intervals and elevated reasoning marker frequencies. \
At the end it shows how timing-based defense mechanisms can expose automated \
harvesting."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982002615994177*^9, 3.982002653218176*^9}, {
  3.9820028054810905`*^9, 3.9820029813905945`*^9}, {3.9820042370311584`*^9, 
  3.982004242091772*^9}, {3.982004274672888*^9, 
  3.9820043456640854`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bc578242-23d8-bb4c-be8e-\
f7ade6f8639b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the ",
 ButtonBox["GitHub repository",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://github.com/ahmedco31/llm-distillation"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://github.com/ahmedco31/llm-distillation"],
 " you can find python code used to create and organise prompts data file \
divided into 5 categories: abstract (280), code_simple (280), commonsense \
(280), logic_chain (380), and math_basic (380) from ",
 ButtonBox["gsm8k data",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://huggingface.co/datasets/openai/gsm8k"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://huggingface.co/datasets/openai/gsm8k"],
 " and templates."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98200304197447*^9, 3.982003477705139*^9}, {
   3.9820038040045414`*^9, 3.982003870696724*^9}, {3.982003906838888*^9, 
   3.9820039079022217`*^9}, 3.982047844443798*^9, {3.9820478863334866`*^9, 
   3.982048084364731*^9}, {3.9820906371653175`*^9, 3.9820906688850937`*^9}, {
   3.9820907566389904`*^9, 
   3.982090759229925*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3eb57bd7-6c24-2f4a-9170-\
20102e82c45b"],

Cell["\<\
Then I used this example prompt data to collect the 1600 responses from \
gpt-40 (1200 prompts) and gpt-4o-mini (400 prompts) to create the responses \
data file responses_openai.csv and make this analysis.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98200304197447*^9, 3.982003477705139*^9}, {
