2.\n- 20 is 10 multiplied by 2.\n- 40 is 20 multiplied by 2.\n\nEach term is \
double the previous term. Therefore, the pattern is to multiply the previous \
term by 2.\n\nFollowing this pattern, the next term after 40 will be:\n\n40 \
\[Times] 2 = 80.\n\nThe next number in the sequence is 80.", {54, 6}]], 
