gcd(48, 18)\\nprint(result)  # Output: 6\\n```\\n\\nThis function uses the \
Euclidean algorithm, where the gcd of two numbers a and b is computed \
recursively by replacing the larger number with the remainder of the division \
of a by b until one of the numbers becomes zero.\""}}, 
