nums2):\\n    # Combine the two arrays\\n    merged = sorted(nums1 + \
nums2)\\n    n = len(merged)\\n    \\n    # Calculate the median\\n    if n % \
2 == 0:\\n        median = (merged[n // 2 - 1] + merged[n // 2]) / 2\\n    \
else:\\n        median = merged[n // 2]\\n    \\n    return median\\n\\n# \
Example usage:\\nnums1 = [1, 3]\\nnums2 = \
[2]\\nprint(findMedianSortedArrays(nums1, nums2))  # Output: 2.0\\n\\nnums1 = \
[1, 2]\\nnums2 = [3, 4]\\nprint(findMedianSortedArrays(nums1, nums2))  # \
