              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To remove similar rows from a given tuple matrix, you can \
create a function that utilizes a set to track unique rows. Here's how to \
implement this in Python:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
remove_similar_rows(matrix):\\n    # Use a set to store unique rows\\n    \
unique_rows = set()\\n    \\n    # Create a list to store the result\\n    \
result = []\\n    \\n    for row in matrix:\\n        # Convert the row to a \
tuple (if it's not already a tuple)\\n        row_tuple = tuple(row)\\n       \
 # Check if the row is not already in the set\\n        if row_tuple not in \
unique_rows:\\n            unique_rows.add(row_tuple)  # Add the row to the \
set\\n            result.append(row)  # Add the row to the result\\n    \\n   \
 return result\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nmatrix = (\\n    (1, 2, 3),\\n    (4, \
5, 6),\\n    (1, 2, 3),  # similar row\\n    (7, 8, 9),\\n    (4, 5, 6)   # \
similar row\\n)\\n\\nunique_matrix = \
remove_similar_rows(matrix)\\nprint(unique_matrix)\\n```\\n\\n### Final \
Answer\\nThe function `remove_similar_rows(matrix)` removes similar rows from \
a given tuple matrix and returns a list of unique rows.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
