             "To remove similar rows from a given tuple matrix, you can \
create a function that utilizes a set to track unique rows. Here's how to \
implement this in Python:\n\n```python\ndef remove_similar_rows(matrix):\n    \
# Use a set to store unique rows\n    unique_rows = set()\n    \n    # Create \
a list to store the result\n    result = []\n    \n    for row in matrix:\n   \
     # Convert the row to a tuple (if it's not already a tuple)\n        \
row_tuple = tuple(row)\n        # Check if the row is not already in the set\n\
        if row_tuple not in unique_rows:\n            \
