takes the coefficients \\\\( a \\\\), \\\\( b \\\\), and \\\\( c \\\\) of the \
quadratic equation and returns `True` if the roots are reciprocal and `False` \
otherwise. It also checks if \\\\( a \\\\) is non-zero to ensure a valid \
quadratic equation.\""}}, 
