              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Let's calculate how much money Tobias earned over the past \
three months.\\n\\n1. **Allowance for 3 months**: \\n   \\\\[\\n   3 \
\\\\text{ months} \\\\times 5 \\\\text{ dollars/month} = 15 \\\\text{ \
dollars}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n2. **Earnings from mowing lawns**: \\n   Tobias \
mowed 4 lawns at $15 each:\\n   \\\\[\\n   4 \\\\text{ lawns} \\\\times 15 \\\
\\text{ dollars/lawn} = 60 \\\\text{ dollars}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n3. **Total \
earnings before shoveling driveways**:\\n   \\\\[\\n   15 \\\\text{ dollars \
(allowance)} + 60 \\\\text{ dollars (mowing)} = 75 \\\\text{ dollars}\\n   \\\
\\]\\n\\n4. **Cost of shoes**: \\n   The shoes cost $95. After buying them, \
he has $15 left:\\n   \\\\[\\n   95 \\\\text{ dollars (shoes)} + 15 \\\\text{ \
dollars (remaining)} = 110 \\\\text{ dollars}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n5. **Total \
money earned**:\\n   Tobias earned $110 in total.\\n\\n6. **Calculating the \
amount earned from shoveling driveways**:\\n   The total amount from mowing \
lawns and allowance is $75. Therefore, he must have earned the remaining \
amount from shoveling driveways:\\n   \\\\[\\n   110 \\\\text{ dollars \
