              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Let the number of large animals be \\\\( x \\\\). Then, the \
number of small animals is \\\\( 3x \\\\) since Loraine made three times as \
many small animals.\\n\\nEach large animal requires 4 sticks of wax, so the \
total sticks used for large animals is:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n4x\\n\\\\]\\n\\nEach \
small animal requires 2 sticks of wax, and since there are \\\\( 3x \\\\) \
small animals, the total sticks used for small animals is:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n2 \
\\\\cdot 3x = 6x\\n\\\\]\\n\\nAccording to the problem, Loraine used 12 \
sticks of wax for small animals:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n6x = 12\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNow, solve \
for \\\\( x \\\\):\\n\\n\\\\[\\nx = \\\\frac{12}{6} = 2\\n\\\\]\\n\\nThis \
means Loraine made \\\\( 2 \\\\) large animals. Therefore, the number of \
small animals is:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n3x = 3 \\\\cdot 2 = 6\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNow, \
