Third butcher: \\\\( x \\\\) packages \\\\( \\\\times 4 \\\\) pounds/package \
= \\\\( 4x \\\\) pounds\\n\\nThe total weight of the beef delivered by all \
three butchers is given to be \\\\( 100 \\\\) pounds. Therefore, we can set \
up the equation:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n40 + 28 + 4x = 100\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNow, combine \
the constants:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n68 + 4x = 100\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNext, isolate \\\\( 4x \
