              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find out how many people were on the ship the monster ate \
in the first hundred years, we can set up the problem as follows:\\n\\n1. Let \
\\\\( x \\\\) be the number of people on the ship that was consumed in the \
first hundred years.\\n2. Each subsequent ship has twice as many people as \
the last one. Therefore:\\n   - The second ship (after 100 years) had \\\\( \
2x \\\\) people.\\n   - The third ship (after 200 years) had \\\\( 4x \\\\) \
people.\\n\\nNow, we can sum the total number of people over the three \
hundred years:\\n\\n\\\\[\\nx + 2x + 4x = 7x\\n\\\\]\\n\\nAccording to the \
