\\text{Bobbie's last name length} - 2 = 2 \\times 4 \\)\n   - \\( \
\\text{Bobbie's last name length} - 2 = 8 \\)\n   - \\( \\text{Bobbie's last \
name length} = 8 + 2 = 10 \\)\n\nNow we know Bobbie's last name has 10 \
letters.\n\n3. Samantha's last name has three fewer letters than Bobbie's:\n  \
 - \\( \\text{Samantha's last name length} = 10 - 3 = 7 \\)\n\nThus, the \
